Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Earring
Description: Earring in the shape of a circle. An opening in the circle is about 3 mm in length. The cross-section is semi-cylindrical. The exterior surface is relatively rounded and polished, without any sharp ridges. This type of earring is frequently found in New Kingdom burials.
